ow being used in the "war on terror," the past remains powerfully present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBrainwashingxHistoryx20th century. 0aBrainwashingxHistoryy20th century. 0aCaptivity narratives. 0aCold War in literature. 0aCold War in mass media. 0aCold War in motion pictures. 0aCold WarxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aCold WarxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aDefectionxHistoryx20th century. 0aDefectionxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical prisonersxHistoryx20th century. 0aPolitical prisonersxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular culturexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aPopular culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aRepatriationxHistoryx20th century. 0aRepatriationxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american history.  a20th century american politics.  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  abrainwashing scare.  acaptivity.  acold war mobilization.  acold war.  acommunism.  acommunist enemies.  acultural history.  adefection.  adrug addiction.  aearly cold war america.  agovernment and governing.  agulag consciousness.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  aimprisonment.  aindividual autonomy.  akorean war captivity.  amenticide.  anational security.  apopular culture.  apostwar america.  aprison.  aprisoners.  arepatriation.  arobert vogeler.  aunited states of america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520944794zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97805